<TITLE> RMG workers block Dhaka-Ctg highway </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Narayanganj, Apr 27 (bdnews24.com)  Traffic ground to a halt on the Dhaka-Chittagong and Dhaka-Sylhet highways for four hours on Tuesday due to a blockade of readymade garment workers in Narayanganj. Workers of the Opex Garments took to the streets at around 9am demanding minimum wage of Tk 5,000 and attendance bonus, said Biswas Afzal Hossain, superintendent of police in Narayanganj. The workers lifted the blockade at around 1pm after their employers assured them of meeting their demands, he said. The blockade created heavy traffic gridlock on one of the main arteries of the country's traffic route. b
